"How ever did I get lucky enough to get partnered up with you I'll never 
know."
She held his hand and looked into his eyes.
"I guess my logic and emotion circuits went haywire earlier.  I'll try to 
keep them under control from now on.  I don't want you to get into trouble." 
She smiled at him and her spark jumped a bit.
"Oh, by the way, I was in the lab and came across a little black box. I was 
wondering what is was.  I didn't touch it or anything.  But I didn't 
recognize it as part of your normal equipment. Is is anything important or 
something I shouldn't even worry about?"
